transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thanks for calling Viagra, Clint speaking. How can I help you?

Speaker 2: Yeah, I want to cancel this order. I've never placed it, and I've never even received one order.

Speaker 1: Okay, am I speaking to Terry?

Speaker 2: Yep.

Speaker 1: Okay, so you said you never ordered with us before?

Speaker 2: I've never received a package from you. How's that? And now it just...

Speaker 1: You live at 208-11 Madison Lane?

Speaker 2: Yep, and that's my summer address. I'm not even there. I'm in Florida six months, and I'm in South Dakota six months.

Speaker 1: Do you know how we would get that address and your phone number?

Speaker 2: No, I don't. No, I don't.

Speaker 1: Your medical history?

Speaker 2: Yeah, actually I don't, but I can tell you one thing. I've never received one package, and I've never taken a Viagra.

Speaker 1: That's not the concerning part. The concerning part is that someone would be giving us all your personal information...

Speaker 2: You know what?

Speaker 1: ...and then sending it to your summer house.

Speaker 2: That is concerning. That is concerning.

Speaker 1: The fact that you got the pills, I mean, that's like the last thing.

Speaker 2: Well, the fact is I didn't get the pills.

Speaker 1: Well, of course you didn't. If you didn't order it, that makes perfect sense.

Speaker 2: I want to cancel this, and I want...

Speaker 1: I want to try to figure out, you know, because even if we cancel it and someone's got all your information, what's going to stop them from doing this again?

Speaker 2: There's nobody. There's no... My mail gets forwarded to Florida in the wintertime, and I've never received anything.

Speaker 1: So why you didn't receive these pills?

Speaker 2: I have not. I've never received one of them.

Speaker 1: Yeah, but that doesn't make sense. If you said your pills, everything gets forwarded to your address, sir.

Speaker 2: Yeah, but we still haven't done it.

Speaker 1: I still haven't... I have never received anything, not one time, not from the first order.

Speaker 2: I didn't even know the first order was there until I got a notice yesterday that I know there's another 163.

Speaker 1: And my wife goes, well, there's 163 from October.

Speaker 2: I said, I've never received any of this.

Speaker 1: United States Postal Service does have confirmation of delivery at that address at 1:15 p.m. on October 31st, your first order.

Speaker 2: So that was confirmed.

Speaker 1: So even if it went to your other address, they would have sent that to your new address.

Speaker 2: It's the post office. That's what they do.

Speaker 1: So it makes no sense that you would not receive that.

Speaker 2: All right, so I want to cancel this order.

Speaker 1: Okay, no, we'll cancel it for you, sir. We're just trying to figure out what is going on.

Speaker 2: Yeah, me too. I've never taken a Viagra yet.

Speaker 1: Not that I don't want to try it, but you know what? You've got to get them before you can try them.

Speaker 2: Yeah, I know. I'm confused on how we would have even ended up sending them there too, sir.

Speaker 1: You know, we did get a lot of information here. It's not easy to do this by accident.

Speaker 2: This is actually a very hard thing to do, you know what I mean?

Speaker 1: So we can reship these out to you if you want to try them, maybe, possibly.

Speaker 2: No, you know what? I've already went with – now you guys aren't related with Roe, right?

Speaker 1: No, Roe is a very dangerous company that's killing people. I would not take pills from them.

Speaker 2: But Viagra's okay?

Speaker 1: Yeah, Viagra from the Viagra company is FDA approved from the federal government.

Speaker 2: I would say that's okay compared to Roe and Friday Plans.

Speaker 1: And none of them are FDA approved by the government.

Speaker 2: You could put registered. They're trying to be, but they're not because it's a very dangerous medication.

Speaker 1: We're the only company that sells FDA approved product.

Speaker 2: And it comes from France because that's where Viagra was created.

Speaker 1: This all comes from the actual creators of Viagra, not a company that's making a fake version of it.

Speaker 2: So yes, we have the safest medication on the market.

Speaker 1: So, you know, not really sure what's going on here.

Speaker 2: Well, I don't – I'm not saying that I didn't put my information in, but I can verify you.

Speaker 1: I have never received one package, and I've never tried one of your products

Speaker 2: because I've never had a Viagra to date.

Speaker 1: That's very odd, sir.

Speaker 2: It's very odd.

Speaker 1: And like I said, once it – I didn't even realize it the first time

Speaker 2: until I got a notification yesterday through PayPal that I've been charged $163.

Speaker 1: And then I said, oh, they're sending it to South Dakota again.

Speaker 2: I said, I'm not even in South Dakota.

Speaker 1: Well, we wouldn't know that unless told otherwise.

Speaker 2: I mean, did you place it – I mean, was this placed online or did someone call?

Speaker 1: Because, I mean, if someone did this online on their own in their computer in their house,

Speaker 2: and, I mean, we had no control over any of this.

Speaker 1: The order was just –

Speaker 2: Right, right.

Speaker 1: So whatever address they put is the address they put.

Speaker 2: So if no one gives us a different address, then we don't know that you're not there.

Speaker 1: That's definitely the correct address.

Speaker 2: Well, I'm not sure why it wasn't delivered, sir.

Speaker 1: We have confirmation from the United States Postal Service that it was delivered.

Speaker 2: Wow.

Speaker 1: You know what?

Speaker 2: That's another issue in itself.

Speaker 1: Well, we can provide you with the information with the post office so you can verify for yourself.

Speaker 2: I mean, they did deliver this stuff to that address.

Speaker 1: So it seems like you've got multiple issues going on.

Speaker 2: You've got someone giving you information out.

Speaker 1: You've got someone stealing packages from your door.

Speaker 2: Yeah.

Speaker 1: Yeah, it sounds like you've got a lot going on there, sir.

Speaker 2: We'll just go ahead and cancel you out because we don't want to keep charging you for stuff you're not getting.

Speaker 1: That would be fantastic.

Speaker 2: All right, you have a good day, okay?
